 thought, according to feminist ideals, then from a purely logical(?) standpoint
, it becomes necessary that critiques come from within the discipline, as
 they are the most effective in that case...plus, who else can effect change?
 grassroots critical science is the only (I think) effective way to have
 change in the sciences -- towards a holistic and self-aware science
\end_layout

